Solution 	  The number of electrons surrounding the central iodine atom is 7 electrons from the iodine atom plus 1 from each chlorine atom yielding a total of 10 electrons which is 5 pairs. Therefore, the electronic geometry is trigonal bipyramidal. Since only three of the electron pairs are shared, the molecular geometry is T-shaped. 
